<h1 class="display-font">Dirty Hill 2020</h1>
<p><time>April 1st, 2020</time></p>

<p>
  On March 1, 2020 the First International Mountain Board Championship Costa Rica Dirty Hill 2020 was held in Costa
  Rica, the same place in the Association for the Conservation of the Hills in Escazú (CODECE), Barrio El Carmen in San
  José. The organization was in charge of the Mountainboarding Association and had the support of Techno NATURE, INTI
  lifestyle, TRACKTOR Mountainboard Company, Mi Parcela video bar & restaurant, Jkmo and DRP.
</p>
<p>
  The championship included 3 modalities: Freestyle Big Air, Boarder cross and Downhill in the Amateur and Masters
  categories and it was intended to arouse interest in the practice of this sport, both in Costa Rica and in other
  countries.
</p>

<figure class="yt-video-wrapper">
  <iframe class="yt-video" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/65A-EhWwgAE" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>
  <figcaption class="yt-video-caption">
    The official video
  </figcaption>
</figure>

<p>
  The activity had representatives in addition to Costa Rica, from countries such as: Colombia, Guatemala, Argentina,
  Nicaragua, Belgium and France. Among the participants there was also a female representative for this occasion, so it
  is expected that more women will be attracted to this sport and want to join the group of people who practice it.
</p>
<p>
  The activity had the presence of a First Aid Post, as well as private Security.
</p>
<figure class="photo-wrapper">
